one of thsoe with epic pet AND throwing all my mana into Pet heals.. thats WITH the pets 50pt DS on and NO I am NOT wanting fear kiting nerfed or anything)<BR>Mages.. we solo yeah.. and we solo ok. and with epic it DOES get easier.. but its still sucks thanks to xp penalty. (Only thing that pisses me off atm is that xp thing.. I have no issues with the class of mages as a whole.. just strikes me Badly that whats supposed to be our class focus.. pets.. and we get penalized for using them???)</P><P>The only thing I WISH as a mage that made us more useful is a niche..<BR>Mages don't really have one. I don't know about necros.. but the one lvl 60 necro I know in my guild seriously ROCKS on raids, etc.</P><P>On a typical raid I get there and do the following:</P><P>a) Summon a crap load of Blankets.. go oom.. repeat rinse.. etc.<BR>b) Summon a crap load of Mod Rods...Go oom.. repeat rinse.. Etc.<BR>c) Hope that what we are raiding I can hit with a spell of some kind for dmg.. I say I run maybe 50% here.. maybe.<BR>e) CoTH latecomers.. those who get lost.. bad pulls, etc.</P><P><BR>The issue for ME and most mages is this:</P><P>a) Blankets? nice.. but after I summon them.. who needs me?<BR>b) Mod ROds? Mod rod II is very nice.. but .. 60 chanter.. MGB.. Kei.. nuff said.  And after buff time.. rarely used. <BR>c) Spell dmg on mobs? Um.. WIZZY TIME.. adn Necros to some extent as well.. I know the warlock in AoC gets some GOOD dot dmg done on raids.. <BR>e) CoTh? I like the spell.. but damn.. if I had wanted to be a taxi I'd have been a wizzy *heh* (J/k) Seriously.....CoTH was one spell we at least were ALWAYS needed for.. but verant doesn't like the spell.. its easy to abuse it. Though nothings happend to it recently, the 15 min recast rumor is still rampant.</P><P>I have no niche.. all I do can be done by others.. or before teh actual fighting. And you and I know.. pathing sucks in EQ. Pets being how they work pay this price. Many times I've wanted to use a pet on a raid.. and many times I've been told NO.. pathing problems. I KNOW how to control my pet.. I kNOW how to use summon companion and reclaim off my wristband to stop him before he pulls a train. But quite simply the fear for non mages remains that a pet on a raid will kill them all. It does happen.. I summoned a pet one time in Fear.. no issue.. safe spot.. Summoned him.. 3 secs later he was gone.. I was WTF??!!?!? I get summoned by draco and die watching my pet wander off. How he got there I'll never know. I could /report it.. but we know Verant.. we know what would happen.. um.. nothing. 8)</P><P><BR>Basically.. (man this thing is the longest post I've ever typed *heh*)</P><P>Mages are upset more for the fact that we feel we have no ROLE in EQ. While we can do some nice stuff all of our skills can be replaced quite well by other classes.. and sometimes better than we can. While I personally don't have an issue with DC, I can see how some mages might. Pets (epic pet in particular) was a source of pride for us.. it was one thing we really had to make us diffrent. DC sorta upset those ppl.. Beastlord pets? Pleazzzzeee.. I watched my burnout IV lvl 57 earth beat the SNOT out of a fully buffed 60 Beastlord pet. Earth pet smacked him around like a coke addict on a 1970's porno. I have a BST twink.. I like the class a ton. But there pets aren't as good as a mages. </P><P>I can live with my class as it is.. I like playing a mage or I wouldn't be playing still. I find it hard sometimes.. then I go play a twink.. or play a diffrent game. (Dug out good ol SimTower the other day.. I sued to play that thing for DAYS *L*)</P><P>Its the XP penalty that gets me.. and I Imagine it kinda makes some necros kinda not happy as well sice they have somewhat the same issue. </P><P>I posted this for one reason.. Not all mages are idiots. 8) I take what I can do and go with it.. and hope things get changed. But I had to respond to the rather overpowered view of mages I saw vented here. Trust me.. it ain't so.</P><P>Wildet Manaweaver<BR>Rodcet Nife<BR>Archons of Chaos<BR>Mage of the 57th and 3/4</P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
